WEBVTT

00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:09.885
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.761 --> 00:00:13.681
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:16.726
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.771
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:00.853 --> 00:01:02.313
Oh Prince...

00:01:03.105 --> 00:01:06.442
Oh Prince of the eternally unforgiven...

00:01:08.319 --> 00:01:11.822
We greet you with honor to
marvel at what you have become.

00:01:25.586 --> 00:01:29.090
We shall meet again in another world...

00:01:33.844 --> 00:01:36.305
We are your kinsmen...

00:02:01.747 --> 00:02:03.707
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:02:03.874 --> 00:02:05.626
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:09.380
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:02:09.672 --> 00:02:11.799
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:02:11.924 --> 00:02:13.884
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:02:14.009 --> 00:02:16.053
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:02:16.303 --> 00:02:17.930
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:02:18.139 --> 00:02:21.559
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:02:22.268 --> 00:02:25.187
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:02:25.938 --> 00:02:26.564
<i>I...</i>

00:02:26.939 --> 00:02:27.690
<i>... can...</i>

00:02:27.815 --> 00:02:29.900
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:02:30.025 --> 00:02:30.943
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:31.068 --> 00:02:31.902
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:32.027 --> 00:02:33.696
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:33.904 --> 00:02:34.822
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:35.072 --> 00:02:35.823
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:35.948 --> 00:02:37.783
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:38.075 --> 00:02:38.951
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:39.076 --> 00:02:39.910
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:40.077 --> 00:02:41.579
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:41.829 --> 00:02:42.913
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:44.039
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:44.081 --> 00:02:44.790
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:44.957 --> 00:02:46.458
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:51.547 --> 00:02:55.551
Infiltration

00:03:25.706 --> 00:03:29.627
Are you sure there's a secret
passage in this dismal place?

00:03:30.002 --> 00:03:31.629
Our sources are reliable.

00:03:32.129 --> 00:03:36.133
If this passage can be found so
easily I'll give up being a mercenary.

00:03:39.470 --> 00:03:40.095
Found it.

00:03:42.014 --> 00:03:43.015
Giving up, huh?

00:03:44.225 --> 00:03:45.017
Pippin.

00:03:59.031 --> 00:04:00.282
There's no mistake.

00:04:00.407 --> 00:04:01.033
This is it.

00:04:01.492 --> 00:04:02.660
Right, let's go.

00:04:02.868 --> 00:04:03.786
Wait a minute.

00:04:05.037 --> 00:04:06.747
I understand that Pippin and
Judeau need to come along...

00:04:07.164 --> 00:04:09.750
...but you're the commander now,
are you sure you should come?

00:04:09.917 --> 00:04:11.418
If something were to happen to you...

00:04:12.253 --> 00:04:14.546
Our mission is to rescue Griffith.

00:04:14.922 --> 00:04:16.590
We have the highest
chance of succeeding...

00:04:16.757 --> 00:04:19.385
...in our mission if all four of our
strongest members take on the operation.

00:04:19.885 --> 00:04:20.844
Yeah, but...

00:04:22.263 --> 00:04:24.139
You're worried, aren't you?

00:04:24.515 --> 00:04:25.891
Don't make me laugh!

00:04:26.016 --> 00:04:29.019
I'm a stronger
swordsman than either of them.

00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:32.481
Don't bring your
personal feelings into this matter.

00:04:32.523 --> 00:04:33.899
Obey your commander's orders!

00:04:37.403 --> 00:04:38.529
Remember...

00:04:38.612 --> 00:04:40.906
...I can still cover your back.

00:04:41.031 --> 00:04:41.865
Don't forget.

00:04:43.742 --> 00:04:44.285
Yeah...

00:04:46.912 --> 00:04:47.621
Let's go.

00:05:14.898 --> 00:05:15.816
Griffith...

00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:18.944
You were always
looking up to the sky...

00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:24.575
...thinking of nothing else
but to keep climbing and soaring...

00:05:26.076 --> 00:05:28.954
A hawk flying alone,
reaching for the highest point...

00:05:31.206 --> 00:05:32.041
That's right...

00:05:32.708 --> 00:05:34.960
You were always
watching us from above...

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:37.087
Never here on the
ground with the rest of us...

00:05:37.838 --> 00:05:40.841
Calm, cool and never missing a beat.

00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:45.721
Do you really need a reason...

00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:48.974
...each time I decide to lay
my life on the line for you?

00:05:50.601 --> 00:05:53.187
Letting nothing stand
in your path to victory...

00:05:53.604 --> 00:05:56.857
Do you think that I am dreadful?

00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:02.863
Griffith couldn't go on without you!

00:06:04.615 --> 00:06:05.949
If that's true...

00:06:06.575 --> 00:06:07.993
If that's the real truth...

00:06:08.494 --> 00:06:09.453
Then I...

00:06:23.467 --> 00:06:24.843
Pull yourself together.

00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:27.262
Griffith will be back soon.

00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:29.598
There's no way in hell I'm going to die...

00:06:29.765 --> 00:06:31.350
...not without seeing Griffith...

00:06:31.975 --> 00:06:34.853
Even if I have a
thousand more stitches in me...

00:06:36.146 --> 00:06:38.107
Ricket, we need some more water.

00:06:38.273 --> 00:06:39.024
Got it.

00:06:41.527 --> 00:06:43.529
When Griffith returns...

00:06:43.654 --> 00:06:46.240
It'll be the
resurrection of the Band of Hawk!

00:06:54.498 --> 00:06:56.291
Everyone is in good spirits...

00:06:57.751 --> 00:07:00.295
Because, Griffith will be back soon...

00:07:03.298 --> 00:07:05.551
As long as Griffith comes back, then...

00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:26.572
A fairy?

00:07:34.329 --> 00:07:35.205
I saw it...

00:07:35.330 --> 00:07:37.916
...with my very own
eyes, there's no doubt.

00:07:45.215 --> 00:07:46.300
The enemy?

00:07:46.425 --> 00:07:47.676
Why at this time?

00:07:50.721 --> 00:07:51.847
Just a little more...

00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:54.475
All we needed was a little more
time and Griffith would be back!

00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:57.686
We can't let them destroy us, not now!

00:08:10.824 --> 00:08:11.742
Hey...

00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:13.619
Where is everyone?

00:08:22.503 --> 00:08:23.504
Run...

00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:34.765
Run...

00:08:36.308 --> 00:08:37.434
Ricket...

00:09:11.218 --> 00:09:12.094
It can't...

00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:14.304
This can't be real!

00:09:42.874 --> 00:09:43.375
What...

00:09:44.001 --> 00:09:45.752
What's going on?

00:09:59.725 --> 00:10:01.977
I'm amazed we learned
about this secret passage.

00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:03.270
We have supporters inside.

00:10:08.358 --> 00:10:09.026
Wait.

00:10:09.735 --> 00:10:11.153
Supporters of the
resistance movement...

00:10:18.368 --> 00:10:19.786
You must be the Band of the Hawk.

00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:21.788
We are at your service.

00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:23.248
I am Caska of the Band of the Hawk.

00:10:23.665 --> 00:10:25.667
What do you mean by supporters?

00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:28.045
They're from Princess Charlotte.

00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:28.670
Oh...

00:10:29.421 --> 00:10:31.173
We don't have very
much time until dawn.

00:10:31.923 --> 00:10:35.052
We must get to where Griffith's
being kept as soon as possible.

00:10:35.177 --> 00:10:35.677
Yes.

00:10:55.405 --> 00:10:57.324
We'll take it from here.

00:11:34.986 --> 00:11:39.074
In this darkness not a single
ray of light can find its way through.

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:44.996
How long have I been
lying here in this darkness?

00:11:48.959 --> 00:11:50.377
For an eternity...

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:52.963
At times it feels like just a moment...

00:11:54.339 --> 00:11:55.966
I feel nothing...

00:11:58.969 --> 00:12:01.763
It's as if my body is floating in space...

00:12:02.389 --> 00:12:06.768
Am I preserving my sanity?

00:12:08.103 --> 00:12:11.481
Or has it already been lost long ago?

00:12:14.276 --> 00:12:15.277
And yet...

00:12:15.986 --> 00:12:18.155
...in this world like a hollow shell...

00:12:18.655 --> 00:12:20.991
...one thing is clear in my mind...

00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:27.748
Him alone...

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:31.293
...like lightning
splitting through the darkness...

00:12:32.294 --> 00:12:35.297
He appears in my mind so vividly.

00:12:37.048 --> 00:12:41.803
Over and over again
like the waves of a tsunami...

00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:43.513
...hatred...

00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:44.806
...friendship...

00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:46.391
...jealousy...

00:12:47.142 --> 00:12:48.059
...frustration...

00:12:48.685 --> 00:12:49.686
...helplessness...

00:12:50.437 --> 00:12:51.438
...affection...

00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:52.814
...sadness...

00:12:54.316 --> 00:12:56.902
They all come
together into a giant vortex...

00:12:57.569 --> 00:13:02.407
They keep my
consciousness from fading away.

00:13:04.451 --> 00:13:09.790
Guts, the cause of my
confinement in this darkness...

00:13:10.582 --> 00:13:11.917
Will now...

00:13:12.542 --> 00:13:15.212
...be the source of my life!

00:13:16.797 --> 00:13:20.300
This man whose life
was once in my hands...

00:13:20.967 --> 00:13:25.222
At what time did I fall under his control?

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:29.851
And now...

00:13:30.852 --> 00:13:35.357
In my mind I see him radiating
so brightly it pierces my eyes.

00:13:37.567 --> 00:13:38.568
Guts!

00:13:51.248 --> 00:13:51.998
Griffith?

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:54.459
Griffith?

00:13:55.836 --> 00:13:57.128
Is he in a different cell?

00:13:57.587 --> 00:14:00.382
No, he has to be
here, on the lowest level.

00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:12.769
Griffith?

00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:13.895
Grif...

00:14:20.777 --> 00:14:21.403
Gri...

00:14:22.153 --> 00:14:23.154
Griffith...

00:14:39.296 --> 00:14:42.299
The tendons in his arms
and legs have been slashed...

00:14:45.302 --> 00:14:46.386
And his tongue...

00:14:47.679 --> 00:14:48.889
Caska, the keys!

00:14:50.932 --> 00:14:51.558
Caska!

00:15:12.037 --> 00:15:12.954
Stay there!

00:15:13.705 --> 00:15:14.706
Stay where you are!

00:15:18.043 --> 00:15:19.461
This isn't possible.

00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:23.673
This can't be Griffith...

00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:39.689
Guts...

00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:41.566
Griffith!

00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:30.156
There's no escaping now...

00:16:33.034 --> 00:16:37.038
The guards and soldiers
will be here any minute...

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:43.169
And in a year, you'll all
be looking just like him...

00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:46.923
You bastard...

00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:52.554
So you're the bastard
who destroyed his body...

00:16:53.013 --> 00:16:54.639
That's right.

00:16:55.056 --> 00:16:57.934
I haven't had that
much fun in a long time.

00:16:58.059 --> 00:17:02.313
You don't come across a
specimen as splendid as him very often.

00:17:02.522 --> 00:17:05.233
When you're as experienced as
I am in the profession of torture.

00:17:05.358 --> 00:17:07.902
...not only do you
appreciate beauty on the surface...

00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:13.533
...but also the beauty that lies beneath
the skin, in tendons, muscles, and veins.

00:17:14.409 --> 00:17:17.245
He really was exquisite.

00:17:18.621 --> 00:17:19.789
There's no use.

00:17:19.873 --> 00:17:23.626
This door is four times
thicker than your average door.

00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:47.567
Don't move!

00:17:47.650 --> 00:17:49.277
Put down your weapons and surrender!

00:17:50.904 --> 00:17:52.572
Stick with me and don't fall back!

00:17:53.782 --> 00:17:54.449
Guts!

00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:07.295
How dare you?

00:18:07.462 --> 00:18:08.463
What the hell are you doing?

00:18:08.546 --> 00:18:09.422
Shoot them!

00:18:22.477 --> 00:18:23.603
You idiots!

00:18:23.728 --> 00:18:24.687
Who said to retreat?

00:18:24.813 --> 00:18:25.855
Hold your ground!

00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:32.445
Hurry!

00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:35.115
What's taking them so long!

00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:38.368
There's thirty of our
soldiers after just four of them!

00:18:38.493 --> 00:18:39.744
How can it be so difficult?

00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:41.621
Yes, but sir...

00:18:41.746 --> 00:18:44.499
...they're led by that
man, the hundred-man killer!

00:18:44.624 --> 00:18:45.625
Don't be stupid!

00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:49.712
You don't expect them to come here
just to rescue their commander, do you?

00:18:49.754 --> 00:18:50.505
No...

00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:54.509
Besides, myths like that
are born in times of war...

00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:57.762
...when stories get exaggerated.

00:18:58.346 --> 00:19:03.726
There is no man in the world who can
kill a hundred armed men with his sword.

00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:06.646
At the very most, ten soldiers.

00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:21.411
That is definitely him...

00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:23.663
The ruthless commander
of the Band of the Hawk...

00:19:23.788 --> 00:19:24.414
Guts!

00:19:24.789 --> 00:19:26.541
It's Hundred-Man Guts himself!

00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.880
Surround him,
what are you waiting for?

00:19:32.005 --> 00:19:33.298
Seize him!

00:19:33.506 --> 00:19:34.174
But sir...

00:19:34.632 --> 00:19:35.633
You idiots!

00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:40.430
He's been swinging his huge sword
around and chasing after our men...

00:19:40.513 --> 00:19:42.056
He's out of breath.

00:19:43.308 --> 00:19:44.809
You fools!

00:19:45.059 --> 00:19:50.273
If your enemy sees you
hesitating, you've already lost the battle.

00:19:50.690 --> 00:19:54.944
Taste battle, and pay for this
lesson on ruthlessness with your life.

00:19:58.948 --> 00:19:59.699
Guts!

00:20:05.538 --> 00:20:06.414
Advance!

00:20:12.462 --> 00:20:13.296
Where are they?

00:20:13.463 --> 00:20:15.215
See, it's too much
for just the four of them...

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:16.341
No...

00:20:16.466 --> 00:20:17.842
You're wrong, they'll be back.

00:20:18.426 --> 00:20:19.469
I'm sure of it.

00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:33.483
Guts...

00:21:13.648 --> 00:21:15.400
What a disgrace!

00:21:15.525 --> 00:21:19.654
If we let them get away
the King will not forgive us.

00:21:20.863 --> 00:21:21.656
Pursue them!

00:21:22.115 --> 00:21:24.534
We'll get ahead of them
and wait for their arrival.

00:21:24.742 --> 00:21:25.285
Yes sir!

00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:05.283
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.408 --> 00:22:08.953
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:10.163 --> 00:22:12.957
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:13.082 --> 00:22:15.918
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:19.213
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.339 --> 00:22:20.465
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.590 --> 00:22:23.676
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:27.805
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.930 --> 00:22:31.184
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.476 --> 00:22:34.729
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:35.229 --> 00:22:38.107
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.858 --> 00:22:41.861
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.737 --> 00:22:45.490
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:07.011 --> 00:23:09.013
Next Episode

00:23:09.847 --> 00:23:11.516
Beloved thoughts...

00:23:11.641 --> 00:23:12.850
The will to live...

00:23:13.351 --> 00:23:16.896
All is lost at the end of their journey.

00:23:17.522 --> 00:23:19.148
Their hearts bleed...

00:23:19.482 --> 00:23:22.652
...full of regret and
sorrow as they stand idle.

00:23:23.277 --> 00:23:26.614
In this world, will mankind survive?

00:23:27.407 --> 00:23:31.619
Can only the wind
foretell the end of their dreams?

00:23:34.038 --> 00:23:37.041
Eve of the Feast

